In this project,machine learning-based classifiers are developed to predict customers' attrition. The data set which is provided in the course "Deep Learning A-Z 2023: Neural Networks, AI & ChatGPT Prize " contains details of a bank's customers and the target variable is a binary variable indicating that whether or not the particular customer left the bank (closed his account). The features used to create machine learning 's models is defined as follows:

Credit Score
Geography : the country where the customer lives
Gender
Age
Tenure: the length of time for which the account is valid or active.
Balance
Number Of Products: products means that saving Chequing accounts and customers credit account
HasCrCard: whether or not the customer has credit cart
IsActiveMember: whether or not the customer logged onto online banking or have any transactions
Estimated Salary
